                  "tag": "a",
                  "link": "https://codepen.io/alanizcreative/pen/poPLMyJ/56845539ce4080e0db765bea698bfbb0",
                  "content": "CodePen"
                },
                {
                  "content": " with the aim of getting something for stakeholders to review quicker. Later.com is a static Gatsby generated site. At the time, I wasn't very experienced with the React library so thought this approach would work best. However, the process of moving code over and site build factors (eg. global CSS interfering with LaterCon styles&ndash;Styled Components later circumvented this issue) was time consuming and diminished earlier gains."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "renderType": "rich-text",
              "tag": "p",
              "content": [
                {
                  "content": "As mentioned earlier, transitions and animations were important parts of the overall vision for the landing page. We started off small with button animations inspired by "
                },
                {
                  "tag": "a",
                  "link": "https://tympanus.net/Development/ButtonHoverStyles/",
                  "content": "Codrops"
                },
                {
                  "content": " The slight scaleY and skew effects in these examples worked well with the subtle morphing quality we were looking to achieve. This formed the base for many on scroll transitions like the text reveals. In terms of accessibility, we made sure to respect users' motion preferences with reduced motion queries as well as hiding repetitive markup (eg. individual spans for letters) from the accessibility tree. We also tested it with JavaScript disabled (mainly for SEO purposes as search engine bots might not execute all JavaScript code) to make sure all content was still visible."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
